content.comments: NOTES: LNS notes: Possible Physeter catodon in background, first clicks heard at start of recording. 13 Sept. 2002 SAS. Tape notes: At 30 fath. edge. Engines on. Also distant sperm.  SEAOCEAN. Other Behaviors: Clicks, Squeals, Whistles.

NOTES: LNS note: The recordist's notes for this reel indicate three separate cuts of Delphinus delphis, but the break points could not be identified during archival. Counter readings were given in the notes. Assuming there is a linear relationship between the counter and real time, 1 mark is approximately equal to 1 second. The breaks should appear at roughly 6 minutes and 16 minutes. 8 July 2002 SAS. Tape notes: "Counter 0000-0353, Four porpoise about bow, then move off after several minutes. Only Intermittent pulses heard; no cries, etc. Ship at 4 knots, sea 4, heavy swells. No movies taken. Saw 10 Finback whales close; no sounds. We were busy with Gulf III sampler. Caution: RF signal present. Counter 0352-0936. Many of same type porpoise above, 4 hours later. Took 65 foot of color movies. Sounds are fair. Ship at 10-12 knots. Counter 0936-1268. Many of same above, four hours later. No movies; dusk. Sounds are good. Ship at 12 knots. Movie shows Delphinus delphis." SEAOCEAN.

NOTES: LNS notes: The date indicated on the reel box is 14 August 1964, but the tape notes, earlier cuts, and later cuts all suggest the date could be 18 August 1964. SAS 28 June 2002. Tape notes: "Ship at 6 knots." SEAOCEAN. Other Behaviors: Whistles.
NOTES: Tape notes:  "Short piece of common dolphons, just entered main Gulf Strem, heavy swells, overcast." SEAOCEAN. Other Behaviors: Whistles.
